      "span_text": "Hypothetical populations, with plausible rates covering a range of trajectories to stationarity, are then examined, along with the urban and rural population of Mexico, 1970, in order to quantify the magnitude of the growth attributable to spatial momentum. where ρ j represents the rate of natural increase (i.e. the birth rate minus the death rate) in state j, and m ij represents the rate of interregional transfer from state i to state j."
